    hadithEnglish:
      'Abu Masud Al-Badri (May Allah be pleased with him) reported:\nWe were sitting in the company of Sad bin Ubadah (May Allah be pleased with him), when the Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) came to us. Bashir bin Sad said: O Messenger of Allah! Allah has commanded us to supplicate for you, but how should we do that? The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) kept silent. We were much perturbed over his silence and we wished he did not asked him this question. The Messenger of Allah (ﷺ) said, Say: O Allah, exalt the mention of Muhammad and the family of Muhammad as you exalted the family of Ibrahim. And bless Muhammad and the family of Muhammad as You blessed the family of Ibrahim. You are the Praised, the Glorified, and the method of greeting (i.e., Salam) is as you know.\n\n[Muslim].\n',
